Compare More Than Interest Rates
While interest rates often receive the most attention, they should never be the only factor when evaluating financing options. Buyers should also compare closing costs, loan terms, repayment flexibility, customer service, and overall lender experience.
Understanding the complete cost of borrowing provides a more accurate picture of long-term affordability. A slightly different interest rate may be worthwhile if it comes with lower fees or better loan features that support your financial goals.
